1. Add item to array.

const notes = ['Note 1', 'Note 2', 'Note 3'];

//push will add an item to an array.
notes.push('Note 4');

2. Remove item from array, we will use splice, we will need to proviude the index of the item along with how many we want to remove. 

//We are removing 1 item from the array at index 0
notes.splice(0, 1);

3. We can also use splice to replace an item in an array with a new item.

const notes = ['Note 1', 'Note 2', 'Note 3'];

//This will rtemove the first item of the array and add a new one.
notes.splice(0, 1, 'New Note 1');

notes.forEach(element => {
  console.log(element);
});
